# Email templates

Read `src/als_intel/emails/README.md` before adding or changing templates.

- Use `theme.py` constants — never hardcode brand colors in templates
- Wrap HTML in `render_email_layout()` — never build full HTML documents in template files
- Every template returns `EmailContent` with both `plain_text` and `html`
- Table-based markup; inline styles only; no `<style>` blocks or external CSS
- Add tests in `tests/test_emails.py` for every new template
- Preview multipart emails in Mailpit (`make docker-dev-up`, http://localhost:8025)
